---
import { ArrowUpRight, GithubLogo, GameController } from '@phosphor-icons/react/dist/ssr';
---

<section class="section" id="projects">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <span class="eyebrow">// projects</span>
      <h2>Things I've Built</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="projects-list">

      <article class="project-item flagship">
        <div class="project-header">
          <div class="project-kicker"><strong>// flagship — unguided analysis</strong></div>
          <h3>News NLP Pipeline</h3>
          <div class="project-metric-badge">Metric: 350k+ articles processed</div>
        </div>
        <p>
          I wanted to know what Dawn actually writes about, so I built a pipeline for unguided analysis. Runs the raw data through BERTopic for topic modeling, spaCy for NER, and a classifier for sentiment. No labels, no supervision. The structure emerges from the text itself.
        </p>
        <p class="tech-stack" aria-label="Project tags">
          <span class="tech-pill">Python</span>
          <span class="tech-pill">NLP</span>
          <span class="tech-pill">spaCy</span>
          <span class="tech-pill">BERTopic</span>
        </p>
        <div class="project-links">
          <a href="https://github.com/umerkniazi/news-nlp-pipeline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <GithubLogo aria-hidden="true" weight="bold" /> GitHub
          </a>
          <a href="https://news-nlp-pipeline.streamlit.app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <ArrowUpRight aria-hidden="true" weight="bold" /> Streamlit App
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="project-item">
        <div class="project-header">
          <div class="project-kicker">// computer vision — edge case QA</div>
          <h3>GB Wildlife Classifier</h3>
          <div class="project-metric-badge">Metric: 98.16% val accuracy</div>
        </div>
        <p>
          Frozen early layers, custom 3-class head trained on three endangered Himalayan species from Gilgit-Baltistan. The real work was stress-testing out-of-distribution data, adding an 80% confidence threshold to catch unknowns, and documenting failure modes where visual and taxonomic similarity trips the model.
        </p>
        <p class="tech-stack" aria-label="Project tags">
          <span class="tech-pill">Python</span>
          <span class="tech-pill">PyTorch</span>
          <span class="tech-pill">Computer Vision</span>
          <span class="tech-pill">Streamlit</span>
        </p>
        <div class="project-links">
          <a href="https://github.com/umerkniazi/gb-wildlife-classifier" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <GithubLogo aria-hidden="true" weight="bold" /> GitHub
          </a>
          <a href="https://gb-wildlife-classifier.streamlit.app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <ArrowUpRight aria-hidden="true" weight="bold" /> Streamlit App
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="project-item">
        <div class="project-header">
          <div class="project-kicker">// machine learning — predictive triage</div>
          <h3>Shelter Outcome Predictor</h3>
          <div class="project-metric-badge">Metric: 80k+ intake records modeled</div>
        </div>
        <p>
          Trained a Random Forest on data from Austin Animal Center to predict which animals are at risk. Built for recall over precision because a missed at-risk animal is worse than a false alarm. Deployed as a Streamlit app. This one matters to me personally.
        </p>
        <p class="tech-stack" aria-label="Project tags">
          <span class="tech-pill">Python</span>
          <span class="tech-pill">Machine Learning</span>
          <span class="tech-pill">Streamlit</span>
        </p>
        <div class="project-links">
          <a href="https://github.com/umerkniazi/shelter-outcome-predictor" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <GithubLogo aria-hidden="true" weight="bold" /> GitHub
          </a>
          <a href="https://shelter-outcome-predictor.streamlit.app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <ArrowUpRight aria-hidden="true" weight="bold" /> Streamlit App
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <div class="secondary-projects-heading">
        <span class="eyebrow">// other work</span>
      </div>

      <article class="project-item">
        <div class="project-header">
          <div class="project-kicker">// systems — terminal music player</div>
          <h3>WMUS</h3>
        </div>
        <p>
          I use cmus on Linux and needed something similar on Windows. Nothing I tried felt quite right, so I wrote my own. Cmus-inspired, Python-based terminal music player with fuzzy search, vim-style bindings, and metadata caching. It focuses on doing one thing well without getting in the way.
        </p>
        <p class="tech-stack" aria-label="Project tags">
          <span class="tech-pill">Python</span>
          <span class="tech-pill">CLI Tool</span>
          <span class="tech-pill">Systems Programming</span>
        </p>
        <div class="project-links">
          <a href="https://github.com/umerkniazi/wmus" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <GithubLogo aria-hidden="true" weight="bold" /> GitHub
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="project-item side-project">
        <div class="project-header">
          <div class="project-kicker">// game dev — endless runner</div>
          <h3>Waddle Away</h3>
        </div>
        <p>
          An endless runner built in Godot. I made this because I wanted to understand how games actually feel: collision response, frame timing, the gap between technically correct and fun. It taught me more about feedback loops than any ML paper has.
        </p>
        <p class="tech-stack" aria-label="Project tags">
          <span class="tech-pill">Godot</span>
          <span class="tech-pill">Game Development</span>
        </p>
        <div class="project-links">
          <a href="https://github.com/umerkniazi/waddle-away" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <GithubLogo aria-hidden="true" weight="bold" /> GitHub
          </a>
          <a href="https://umerkniazi.itch.io/waddle-away" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <GameController aria-hidden="true" weight="duotone" /> Itch.io
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .section-heading {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.55rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.84rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .projects-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 3.5rem;
    max-width: 680px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding-top: 3rem;
  }

  .project-item {
    border: none;
    border-radius: 0;
    background: transparent;
    box-shadow: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.15rem;
    transition: none;
  }

  .project-item:hover {
    transform: none;
    background: transparent;
    box-shadow: none;
  }

  .project-header {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .project-kicker,
  .project-kicker strong {
    font-family: var(--font-serif) !important;
    font-style: italic !important;
    font-weight: 300 !important;
    font-size: 1.1rem !important;
    color: var(--accent) !important;
    opacity: 0.85;
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
    text-transform: none;
    letter-spacing: normal;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    width: auto;
    justify-self: start;
    align-self: start;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    white-space: normal;
  }

  .project-metric-badge {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    width: fit-content;
    background: var(--surface-strong);
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 2px;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .project-item h3 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .project-item > p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .tech-stack {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .tech-pill {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    background: transparent;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 2px;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    white-space: nowrap;
    transition: all var(--transition-fast);
  }

  .project-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .project-links a {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 0.94rem;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }

  .project-item:hover .project-links a {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .project-links a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 0.2em;
  }

  .secondary-projects-heading {
    border-top: 1px dashed var(--border);
    padding-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-top: -0.5rem;
  }
</style>